article.headline: Nebraska 68, Colorado 49
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Aleks Maric had 17 points, 16 rebounds and six assists to pace Nebraska toward a 22-point halftime lead and 68-49 win over Colorado on Sunday. Nebraska (18-11, 7-9 Big 12) built the big halftime lead by forcing 12 turnovers and holding the Buffaloes to five field goals. Nebraska opened a 15-2 lead on Maric's free throw with 11 minutes remaining in the first half. Colorado (11-19, 3-12) cut the lead to nine twice, but the Huskers closed the half with a 16-3 run. Nebraska went up by 20 on Sek Henry's steal, layup and free throw with just under three minutes left and ended the half with a 3-pointer from Paul Velander that made the score 36-14. Nebraska opened the second half with a 12-4 run, going up by 30 points on Steve Harley's dunk with 14:28 left. Nebraska's biggest lead was 34. Velander finished with 16 points for Nebraska and Harley had 14. Jevon Coney led Colorado with 15 points. Richard Roby, who fouled out with more than nine minutes left, had 12 points, Marcus Hall had 11.
